## Why This Matters

The Markarth Incident is the **pivotal moment** between:
- The Concordat (a theoretically temporary treaty)
- And the Civil War (an armed conflict)

Without Markarth, Ulfric might have continued seeking diplomatic solutions. It was the **betrayal of the promise** that convinced him violence was the only language the Empire understood.

The irony: the Thalmor did not even need to plan this. The Empire sabotaged itself through its own weakness.
